Cool- has been in 90's for a week- outbreak of weeds in Beaulieu lake
Two very heavy rain storms with very strong winds within a week and a half- 4.5" rain
Rain earlier in the morning- 65 degrees.
Very heavy rain all day- 55 degrees.
Temp is 78 degrees.  Lake level: very high
Eurasian milfoil spreading throughout the lakes
Outside temperature is 47 degrees.  Lake level: very high
Weather beautiful- temp. 66 degrees.  Water level was high- is receding
Lake level high after several days of rain.  Weather beautiful- temperature 64 degrees.
65 degrees- clear dry day.  No rain for 3 days.
sunny- breezy- 55F- blue heron fishing from raft
Lots of bluegill.  Dragonflies.  Sunny- 78 F.  Light breeze.
Partly cloudy- hazy.  80 F.  Bluegill.  Turtles.  We have a loon!
Mostly sunny.  75 F.  Light breeze.  Bluegill- bass- turtles.  Lake lowest I've ever seen. :(
temp 74 degrees- mostly sunny- slight breeze

column1: seems to be fewer bluegill than past years
one loon stopped briefly for a swim- then left
lake levels have recovered somewhat from last year's lows

column2: temps in the upper 70's- cloudy with peeks of sun- light breeze

column1: small fish were 'flying' out of the water on southeast shore
water level becoming low again - channel depth 3 - 3.5 feet in middle

column2: temps in upper 70's- full sun- light breeze

column1: observed bluegill- small bass- 5 ducks (mother and 4 ducklings)- 1 small turlte
interesting bird with brown/white vertical stripes and long bill (green heron )

column2: temp is 82 degrees- full sun- light breeze

column1: 4 ducks swimming on lake (mother and 3 ducklings)
still seem to be fewer bluegill and frogs compared with past years
lakes are low - we have gained 3 feet of beach since Memorial weekend

column2: temp 83 degrees- full sun- no wind

column1: lake levels nearly as low as at summer's end 2007

column2: 63 degrees- sunny- light breeze- family of 5 ducks
70 degrees- cloudy with peeks of sun- light wind

column1: lake level lowest we've ever observed - channel to Beaulieu Lake too narrow for pontoons and too shallow for trolling motors
bluegill population down along our shoreline
no frogs- few turtles (heard report of otter in the lake )

column2: 64 degrees- sun mixed with clouds- light breeze

column1: some golf ball-sized blobs of green slimy algae among lily pads

column2: 74 degrees- sun with some clouds- calm

column1: lake is at the lowest level anyone (including lifelong residents) has ever seen...

column2: Sunny clear day- one loon on lake- 4 painted turtles on shore

Sun/cloud mix- 85 degrees- light breeze.  Lake is currently at lowest spring level we've ever experienced.  Channel nearly unnavigable on Beaulieu side.  We have 2 duck families; one has 7 ducklings- and the other has 4.  We have one large goose family and one loon!  The snails are huge this year....
Sky:       thin overcast / slight sun glare
Sky - sunny   Water - very small ripple  Wind - light breeze
SKY: mostly cloudy / WATER: small ripple /  WIND: breezy

Sunny- breezy- 78 degrees.  One duck family - Mom and 6 ducklings.  We have gotten 6-7 inches of rain during June.  Our waterline has come up approx. 18 in. along the sand.  No frogs or turtles ( )  Neighbor reported an otter feeding and lounging in the sun on the swim rafts along the south side of the lake.
100% overcast sky / small ripple on water / winds light and variable
SKY; partly cloudy 50% WATER: small ripple WIND: light breeze

78 degrees- sunny- slight breeze.  Watched eagle catch a fish and eat it in one of Judy Siren's lakefront trees -- how cool.  Some clumps of blue-green algae floating in middle of lake - ick.  Alot of silt moving around down deep.  Finally a few turtles- no frogs on our shoreline.  We have had the wettest July on record - over 7 1/2 inches.
SKY - mostly sunny  WATER - choppy  WIND - fairly windy 5 to 10 mph

column1: Deepest part of lake recorded - 45 feet

column2: 68 degrees- sunny- calm.  Spotted two turtles- lots of Monarch butterflies.  Rainfall continued to be above normal during August.

column1: WIND - light NW less than 5 mph

column2: Daylight Saving Time is now OFF ...

column1: The lake water level is significantly higher that last fall.

column2: 70 degrees; mostly sunny; light breeze.  Tiny round algae suspended in water.  Usual school of bluegill around our dock - all sizes.  Small goose family on southwest pennisula.
SKY- partly cloudy  wind -  less than  2 mph water - very little ripple temp - 79 F

80 degrees; sunny; light breeze.  Lake received nearly 7" of rain during week of June 20- 2011 thru June 24- 2011- so lake water level is continuing to recover.  Duck family - mother- 10 nearly grown ducklings - off south west pennisula.
SKY - mostly cloudy WIND - calm Water - like glass  TEMP - 77 F
75 degrees; sunny; light breeze.  Above average precipitation for year continues to raise lake level to near normal.  Good-sized paint turtle sunning himself on west side of channel.
SKY - partly cloudy  WIND - N 5 to 10 mph  WATER - medium ripple  TEMP - 74 F
78 degrees; sunny; light breeze.  Deer tracks on our beach.  Bass are biting!  2 ducks.  Many red dragon flies.
SKY - mostly clear   WIND - 0 to 2 mph NE  WATER  - like glass TEMP - 61 F
Sky - clear     WIND -  calm      WATER - like glass     TEMP - 57 F

column1: The water level of the lake is the highest it has been since we moved here in May 2005.

column2: SKY=mostly cloudy  WIND-SE 0-5mph  WATER-slight ripple  TEMP-77 F
Sunny- 86 degrees- light breeze- water level normal- water in channel nearly 4 feet deep in middle
Sunny with some clouds- 80 degrees- light north wind
Several ducks and geese on south shore
We have a loon!!  Does not seem very shy- as he will swim within ten feet of us while we swim :)  Love listening to his call...
Sunny- some clouds- 70 degrees- calm.  Pair of mallards.
Sunny- 78 degrees- some hazy clouds- no breeze
Cloudy- 60 degrees- windy- feels like fall.  6 geese swimming.
Partly cloudy. Wind NW  4 to 7 mph.  Temp 60 F SKY - partly cloudy
80 degrees- sun- light breeze.  Pair of loons swimming in middle of the lake.
80 degrees- sun- light breeze.  Loon swimming in middle.  School of crappie.
74 degrees- partly sunny- calm.  Many turtles sunning themsleves on fallen trees at the water's edge.

column1: WATER -  calm ( like this in Koonz- Beaulieu considerably windier and rougher)
There are a lot of tree dropings on the lake near the shore line.
The water level is "EXTREMELY" high. All but a couple of docks are completely under water.
Lake level very high. Many docks still under water.
Lake level is even higher than two weeks ago.

column2: 80 degrees- partly cloudy- calm.  Lake levels higher than we've seen in 18 years.  Needed to raise our dock twice.  Birch trees dying all around perimeter of lake.
74 degrees- overcast chrome-colored sky- rain impending- breeze gusts.  Lake color very green - more so than usual.  Levels continue to rise.

74 degrees- partly cloudy- light breeze.  Many blooms of regular green algae spotted clinging to weeds near the lake bottom all around the shoreline.  Water temp seems higher than normal for this time of year.
Partly cloudy- breezy.  Lake levels highest we have observed in 20 years.  Spotted a blue heron and pair of mallards.  Observed lots of regular algae.

80 degrees- mostly sunny- very breezy.  Koonz water color slightly brown as opposed to its normal slightly green.  Water levels highest we have observed in 20 years.  One lone loon swimming in middle of the lake.
72 degrees- full sun- slightly breezy.  Lake levels still very high.  Also saw 2 turtles sunning on fallen trees along shore.
